WEBVTT

00:01.538 --> 00:12.810
In a season filled with noise, with full calendars, full schedules, and full hands, we can still find ourselves feeling empty.

00:14.111 --> 00:16.754
But Christmas was never meant to be crowded.

00:17.775 --> 00:21.839
It was meant to be clear, simple, uncluttered.

00:23.201 --> 00:28.466
When we make room, we discover the gift that was there all along.

00:35.394 --> 00:36.497
Good morning.

00:36.537 --> 00:39.504
Welcome to Encounter Church.

00:39.524 --> 00:41.610
How many of you are excited to be here today?

00:41.650 --> 00:43.194
Amen.

00:43.294 --> 00:43.635
Amen.

00:43.735 --> 00:48.366
If you are a guest today, we are honored that you've chosen to worship with us.

00:48.387 --> 00:49.409
We're honored that you're here.

00:49.850 --> 00:52.978
As they were talking about a moment ago, please take a moment.

00:53.026 --> 00:57.630
fill that connect card out, that welcome card, help us get to know you just a little bit better.

00:58.291 --> 01:03.535
That helps us, helps you, helps the body of Christ to grow and become what God wants it to be.

01:03.996 --> 01:07.859
All right, well, this morning, I'm excited about today for a couple of reasons.

01:08.319 --> 01:13.664
Number one, because we are joined together by our entire encounter church family.

01:13.684 --> 01:23.012
In fact, this morning, we're going to have not only our online folks with us, but we're gonna have our Lincoln family with us and our Warrensburg family.

01:22.992 --> 01:25.355
with us, can we give them a hand this morning?

01:25.395 --> 01:27.378
Amen.

01:28.359 --> 01:42.497
I love these weeks when we all get to gather together for just a few moments and experience God's Word together and allow His Word to become alive and real in our personal lives.

01:42.598 --> 01:43.739
I say it all the time.

01:44.620 --> 01:52.210
We have to remind ourselves that every word in this book is applicable to our everyday lives.

01:52.866 --> 01:53.767
Come on.

01:53.787 --> 02:01.558
Sometimes we're guilty of trying to do things by ourselves in anybody in the house, anybody at one of our locations or online.

02:01.578 --> 02:05.103
Are we ever guilty of trying to do things by ourselves?

02:05.363 --> 02:05.823
Yeah.

02:06.585 --> 02:13.274
And we say things like, well, you know, they just don't give you a guidebook for that when you leave the hospital and you have kids.

02:13.934 --> 02:17.339
Or when you grab that marriage license, they don't give you a book to help you understand women.

02:18.360 --> 02:19.642
Come on, somebody.

02:19.662 --> 02:21.585
Yeah.

02:21.645 --> 02:22.546
Well, you know what?

02:22.658 --> 02:40.498
God's Word, if we will allow it to really penetrate our lives, it helps to open up the door and open up an avenue to allow God to lead us in a path and in a direction that not only honors Him,

02:41.090 --> 02:46.222
but helps to further his kingdom as we reach beyond ourselves and impact lives around us.

02:46.703 --> 02:53.458
So today we are in part two of a series that we are simply calling the uncluttered

02:53.858 --> 02:54.479
Christmas.

02:54.659 --> 02:57.922
I wanted to stay with this theme of make room.

02:57.942 --> 02:59.803
This has been our theme for 2025.

02:59.823 --> 03:03.887
I wanted to hang out in that just as long as we could.

03:03.947 --> 03:06.849
So we've included that in this series.

03:07.250 --> 03:19.260
It's the uncluttered Christmas, but this morning we're taking the time to look at the idea of what happens when we make room for God in the midst of the busyness of life.

03:19.500 --> 03:23.844
Would you agree with me today that we live in a very hurry up

03:23.824 --> 03:24.705
society.

03:24.725 --> 03:30.473
Everything seems like it's on fire all of the time.

03:30.534 --> 03:34.459
Everything is a urgency moment.

03:34.499 --> 03:35.641
You get that phone call.

03:35.681 --> 03:37.684
The people need you now.

03:37.824 --> 03:39.566
You need a resolution for that.

03:39.927 --> 03:42.050
Now your boss needs an answer for that.

03:42.450 --> 03:46.056
Now you've got to take care of that situation now.

03:46.196 --> 03:50.642
But I want to talk to you today about what would happen

03:51.586 --> 04:01.401
If we would slow down just for a moment and allow the peace of God to rest in our lives.

04:03.504 --> 04:21.010
If we're honest with ourselves, this season that's supposed to be filled with joy and peace and goodness and all of the excitement of the holidays, this season gets cluttered with so many things.

04:21.538 --> 04:25.565
How many of you have had already more than two Christmas parties?

04:28.069 --> 04:28.750
Just us.

04:29.392 --> 04:29.792
Thanks.

04:30.494 --> 04:31.816
There's a couple of this group over here.

04:31.836 --> 04:32.737
I've been to at least two.

04:32.757 --> 04:36.604
I've got another one this coming Tuesday night and more to come.

04:36.664 --> 04:40.771
We pack our schedule full of so many things.

04:40.851 --> 04:44.698
And then we wonder why peace is missing.

04:44.718 --> 04:46.962
I want to take a few moments today.

04:47.426 --> 04:54.616
to discover or maybe rediscover what it means to slow down in a hurry up world.

04:54.856 --> 05:15.986
I believe that every Christian, every person that has a relationship with God has at their disposal a peace that is not able to be comprehended or even explained by this world, but a peace that only God can give.

05:16.642 --> 05:20.808
And what we're going to discover tonight, I'm going to kind of peel back a little bit.

05:20.828 --> 05:43.698
What we're going to discover this morning, rather, it's not that life has to really slow down to find the resolution, but we've got to allow God to walk with us in the moments of life so that His peace guides our steps, so that His peace guides our decisions.

05:44.034 --> 05:48.982
so that his peace sets the pace for our life.

05:50.445 --> 05:59.780
I believe that it's amazing how Christmas this season meant to bring peace oftentimes feels anything but peaceful.

06:01.523 --> 06:03.907
It's like the story of the shepherds.

06:03.947 --> 06:10.738
Do you remember in the Christmas story at the moment when the angels appeared to the shepherds?

06:11.298 --> 06:17.246
Now, if you've heard this portion of the Christmas story before, I want to encourage you see it through new lenses today.

06:17.687 --> 06:20.951
Allow God to really kind of open things up for your life.

06:21.012 --> 06:25.298
If you've never heard this story, really tune in closely today.

06:25.518 --> 06:30.985
I believe that God's going to speak into our lives in just a few moments from his word.

06:31.246 --> 06:32.047
Here's the reality.

06:32.568 --> 06:34.290
We rush from store to store.

06:34.978 --> 06:47.017
We scroll through online sales, plan the parties, wrap the gifts in the cards, and somehow try to squeeze in a few moments to remember the reason for the season.

06:48.178 --> 06:53.727
But truth be told, our Christmas is often chaos at best.

06:54.889 --> 07:03.602
Our calendars may be absolutely jam-packed full, but many times our hearts are empty.

07:04.706 --> 07:12.315
seemingly the faster and the faster that we go, the further and the further away from the peace of God we find ourselves.

07:14.077 --> 07:22.607
So could it be that peace is not something you find when the dust settles and the busyness settles down?

07:22.707 --> 07:28.754
Could it be that peace is found in the one that meets you where you are?

07:30.146 --> 07:34.740
Come on, I want to say that again because that should have got this side excited this morning.

07:36.386 --> 07:39.535
Could it be that peace is not when everything slows down?

07:39.555 --> 07:41.522
Because we excuse our way through, right?

07:41.542 --> 07:44.210
We say things like, well, it's just a season.

07:44.994 --> 07:50.244
When anybody ever used that phrase in their life, it's just a busy season of life.

07:50.264 --> 07:52.789
Eventually, you know, the season is going to be over.

07:53.110 --> 08:01.527
But what I've come to understand is I go from one crazy season to the next crazy season to the next crazy season.

08:01.787 --> 08:05.234
But yet every single season, I say it's just a season.

08:07.650 --> 08:13.537
Could it be that peace isn't necessarily found when the dust settles from the crazy season?

08:13.898 --> 08:24.591
Could it be that peace is found when we ask God, when we invite Him in to the chaos that we find ourselves in?

08:26.112 --> 08:33.642
Could it be that when we open up that door and say, you are welcome here, I make room for you?

08:33.742 --> 08:37.266
Could it be that it's there that we find peace?

08:38.722 --> 08:43.649
Today I wanna look at this story in Luke chapter two.

08:43.709 --> 08:47.214
This is a time and a busy moment for the shepherds.

08:47.254 --> 08:59.490
They were watching their sheep, no doubt they were fending off all of the predators, the wolves, the bears, who knows what, they were chasing the sheep.

08:59.510 --> 09:08.082
They were minding their own business and they find themselves with an encounter with not just an angel,

09:09.506 --> 09:12.430
but a heavenly choir presenting a message.

09:12.531 --> 09:13.612
Take a look at what it says.

09:15.255 --> 09:20.222
That night, there were shepherds staying in the fields nearby, guarding their flocks of sheep.

09:21.304 --> 09:23.567
Suddenly, come on, look at your neighbor, say suddenly.

09:23.607 --> 09:31.519
Suddenly, the angel of the Lord appeared among them and the radiance of the Lord's glory surrounded them.

09:31.579 --> 09:34.303
Now, first off, could you imagine they're on a hillside?

09:34.383 --> 09:38.930
No doubt, they probably had a little campfire, but that was all of the light.

09:39.042 --> 09:40.103
dark out there.

09:40.984 --> 09:47.952
And suddenly the angel of the Lord appears, the glory of the Lord shone around them.

09:48.012 --> 09:52.176
And the Bible says they were terrified.

09:55.400 --> 09:57.582
But the angel reassured them, don't be afraid.

09:58.583 --> 10:04.850
Look what he says, I bring you good news that will bring great joy to all people.

10:05.410 --> 10:11.437
The Savior, yes, the Messiah, the Lord, has been born today in Bethlehem, the city of David.

10:12.298 --> 10:13.899
And you will recognize him by this sign.

10:13.919 --> 10:18.144
You will find the baby wrapped snugly in strips of cloth lying in a manger.

10:18.745 --> 10:29.557
Suddenly the angel was joined by a vast host of others, the armies of heaven praising God and saying, Glory to God in the highest.

10:30.658 --> 10:34.482
And peace on earth to those whom God

10:35.266 --> 10:36.007
is pleased.

10:36.808 --> 10:39.491
I want to take a few moments this morning.

10:39.571 --> 10:49.942
I want to dig into what it looks like when God shows up in a cluttered mess just to bring His peace.

10:50.042 --> 10:52.565
There's three truths that I want to share with you this morning.

10:52.585 --> 11:01.054
Number one is this, God brings peace to ordinary people in unexpected places.

11:02.275 --> 11:04.818
Come on, that should encourage some of us this morning.

11:05.698 --> 11:09.705
God brings peace to ordinary people.

11:09.765 --> 11:13.692
How many of you would consider yourself an ordinary person?

11:15.014 --> 11:17.118
Now some of you are like, I'm nothing but ordinary.

11:17.158 --> 11:19.542
Others are like, I'm not even close to ordinary.

11:19.862 --> 11:20.183
I don't know.

11:20.203 --> 11:28.036
We had one snowman hat going on on the stage, anything but ordinary going on up here this morning patience.

11:28.056 --> 11:28.978
It looked great.

11:29.666 --> 11:32.872
God brings peace to ordinary people in unexpected places.

11:32.912 --> 11:38.321
You see, when we think about peace, oftentimes we think of quiet moments.

11:39.323 --> 11:45.874
When life settles down, maybe you've got the record player playing his plane being Crosby Christmas.

11:47.202 --> 11:49.005
Maybe Gene Autry is on there.

11:49.045 --> 11:52.250
You got some great Christmas music playing in the distance.

11:52.270 --> 11:53.552
You've got candle lights.

11:53.852 --> 11:56.316
The lights are kind of dim in the house.

11:56.336 --> 12:00.822
There's a silent snowfall coming down very gently outside.

12:00.842 --> 12:06.271
You've got a nice warm cup of coffee in your hand and there's a fire in the fireplace.

12:06.311 --> 12:09.475
What an incredible moment that would be.

12:09.535 --> 12:11.959
But here's what I understand.

12:12.139 --> 12:16.626
God didn't show up in a chaos-free moments.

12:18.050 --> 12:25.139
He didn't announce the peace of the king of kings and the Lord of lords to royalty in the palace.

12:25.339 --> 12:28.042
He didn't bring it to the priest in the temple.

12:28.062 --> 12:28.683
Think about this.

12:29.023 --> 12:34.150
God didn't announce the birth of Jesus to powerful and polished people.

12:36.292 --> 12:45.644
But he presented this good news of great joy, this peace for the world to a ragtag group of guys.

12:46.685 --> 12:47.666
They were tired.

12:48.898 --> 12:57.186
They were overworked, overrun, perhaps they were maybe trapped in the spiral of life.

12:57.246 --> 13:05.294
They found themselves in an ordinary day doing the ordinary thing, and yet God showed up for them.

13:07.176 --> 13:11.840
Did you know that Jesus didn't come for those that think they are righteous?

13:13.682 --> 13:14.002
Come on.

13:15.123 --> 13:17.746
He came for messed up people.

13:21.442 --> 13:24.968
I remember the first song that I ever sang as a little guy in churches.

13:25.008 --> 13:26.270
He's still working on me.

13:27.472 --> 13:29.896
I feel like I could sing that song again today.

13:29.997 --> 13:32.401
He's still working on me.

13:32.461 --> 13:35.085
We are all a work in progress.

13:35.967 --> 13:40.274
Come on, look at your neighbor today and say, you are a piece of work.

13:40.642 --> 13:42.624
Yeah, every location.

13:42.944 --> 13:45.387
Come on, participate in this moment.

13:45.667 --> 13:48.030
You are a piece of work.

13:48.110 --> 13:53.556
Aren't you glad that God cares for a piece of work?

13:53.576 --> 14:01.925
Aren't you glad that God cares for ordinary people experiencing ordinary things in the midst of the chaos of life?

14:01.985 --> 14:06.610
I love what Jesus says to the religious folk in his day.

14:07.874 --> 14:11.117
Luke chapter five, he says, healthy people don't need a doctor.

14:13.380 --> 14:19.727
Some of you guys just justified your reason for not going, honey, I told you I didn't need to go to the doctor.

14:21.549 --> 14:24.892
Jesus said, healthy people don't need a doctor.

14:26.114 --> 14:28.636
Healthy people don't need a doctor, sick people do.

14:29.537 --> 14:37.746
I have come to call not those who think they are righteous, but those who know they are sinners and need

14:38.082 --> 14:38.803
to repent.

14:39.884 --> 15:05.074
The shepherds were reminded that peace doesn't wait for the picture perfect, calm, stress free moment, but peace will arrive in the middle of your normal, noisy, perhaps stressful, even loud and rowdy, messy, smelly moments in life.

15:06.754 --> 15:11.681
God desires to show up right where you are today.

15:12.763 --> 15:13.244
Oh, come on.

15:13.584 --> 15:16.789
This should be good news for every one of us this morning.

15:17.209 --> 15:20.454
God sees the craziness of your life.

15:21.836 --> 15:30.008
And yet he stands at the door and he says, can I just come in?

15:31.711 --> 15:33.874
Can I just hang out with you?

15:34.594 --> 15:35.555
for a few moments.

15:35.655 --> 15:39.479
Can we just have a moment together?

15:42.743 --> 15:44.164
Healthy people don't need a doctor.

15:45.626 --> 15:46.327
Sick people do.

15:46.827 --> 15:47.228
Look at this.

15:47.568 --> 15:52.994
The angel of the Lord did not send the message ahead of time to say you need to get ready.

15:54.896 --> 16:00.722
He didn't send a telegram to the shepherds and say to them, well, slow down tonight.

16:01.026 --> 16:07.535
Wait a few moments, schedule out some time because you are going to have the concert of your life.

16:10.399 --> 16:11.800
You didn't say straighten up.

16:11.880 --> 16:15.425
Get yourself all right because God's going to show up.

16:16.306 --> 16:17.488
He wants to send his peace.

16:17.568 --> 16:17.949
No, no, no.

16:18.169 --> 16:18.990
Two things that I see.

16:19.030 --> 16:19.811
Number one is this.

16:20.292 --> 16:23.636
God doesn't wait for peace to give peace.

16:26.740 --> 16:31.026
God doesn't wait for everything to get picture perfect.

16:32.354 --> 16:33.335
to give his peace.

16:33.416 --> 16:35.639
Here's what I love about the Christmas story.

16:35.659 --> 16:37.822
Could you imagine being with the shepherds?

16:38.423 --> 16:40.166
They're going through their regular day.

16:40.206 --> 16:43.771
Like I said a moment ago, they're fighting wolves and bears or you name it.

16:43.992 --> 16:48.318
They're keeping the sheep safe and then suddenly it happens.

16:50.221 --> 16:53.827
The Bible says suddenly an angel of the Lord appeared among them.

16:53.847 --> 16:56.371
The radiance of the Lord's glory surrounded them.

16:56.431 --> 16:58.093
They were terrified.

16:58.734 --> 16:59.535
Now hold on to that word.

16:59.555 --> 17:01.298
We're going to come back in just a moment.

17:01.506 --> 17:05.831
but the angel reassured them, do not be afraid.

17:05.851 --> 17:09.755
Did you see what I saw in this verse?

17:09.775 --> 17:17.183
It doesn't say they gradually appeared, but it says suddenly they showed up.

17:17.464 --> 17:18.304
Here we are.

17:18.324 --> 17:19.846
We have a message.

17:19.946 --> 17:23.330
In fact, we've prepared a little song for you.

17:24.391 --> 17:26.353
This might just be the first singing telegram.

17:26.413 --> 17:26.994
I don't know.

17:28.578 --> 17:31.165
God didn't wait for the calm moment in their lives.

17:31.225 --> 17:32.809
He met them right where they were.

17:32.869 --> 17:33.591
Grab ahold of this.

17:33.852 --> 17:38.585
God meets us where we are, not where we think we need to be.

17:41.592 --> 17:43.698
Some of us are kind of, if I can just

17:44.194 --> 17:53.888
And if I could just align that, if I could just make this happen, then maybe the peace of God will meet me there.

17:53.928 --> 17:57.072
But God says, I want to come in right where you are.

17:57.193 --> 18:01.238
I want to meet you on the hillside as you're watching the sheep.

18:01.579 --> 18:04.763
I want to send my heavenly armies to you.

18:04.824 --> 18:09.330
He desires to meet you in the midst of your chaos.

18:10.850 --> 18:13.354
So yes, God doesn't wait for peace to give peace.

18:13.394 --> 18:16.118
But number two, God offers peace.

18:16.819 --> 18:20.324
And when he does, fear has to leave.

18:21.586 --> 18:28.577
See, some of us, we fail to receive the peace of God because we're consumed by the fear.

18:30.260 --> 18:35.227
Hear the shepherds where they were on the hillside, the angel of the Lord's glory shone around them.

18:35.467 --> 18:39.794
The angel begins to speak to them and the Bible says, they were terrified.

18:41.090 --> 18:45.277
I can imagine, I probably would be much the same as the shepherds that night.

18:46.218 --> 18:51.126
This word fear, it literally means to be seized with alarm.

18:54.451 --> 19:05.970
But God out of his grace, God out of his mercy, he doesn't send the armies of heaven away, but yet he takes a moment and he begins to trade out the fear

19:06.338 --> 19:07.180
for His peace.

19:07.260 --> 19:20.685
The Bible tells us that the peace that Jesus offers is not like the peace of this world, but the peace that He desires to give us will replace the fear in our lives.

19:21.707 --> 19:29.842
See, the world offers peace and that peace is dependent upon circumstances working out just right, but the peace of God

19:30.754 --> 19:36.409
is found when we rest on Him and when we rest in His presence.

19:38.154 --> 19:42.767
Did you know that when we change the environment, it changes where we are?

19:42.807 --> 19:44.391
Come on, look at this.

19:44.532 --> 19:45.394
Stay with me for a second.

19:45.826 --> 19:57.220
When we hang out in the midst of the fear, when we hang out in the midst of the frustration or the discouragement or the doubt or the anxiety or whatever happens to be, we entertain that.

19:57.420 --> 19:58.862
And eventually what happens?

19:59.102 --> 20:02.927
We begin to embody that and take that on as our personality.

20:04.769 --> 20:06.851
Well, you know, I'm just a fearful person.

20:07.832 --> 20:10.396
Oh, I just worry all the time.

20:10.756 --> 20:12.778
Come on, we've all said these things, right?

20:14.100 --> 20:15.762
We identify.

20:16.162 --> 20:17.944
with that, but what would happen?

20:19.886 --> 20:31.720
If in that moment, rather than residing there, we said, Lord, I don't want to necessarily just hang here, but God, I want to go where you are.

20:33.021 --> 20:44.594
The Bible says, in the presence of God, there is fullness of joy, not just a little bit of joy, but a fullness

20:45.250 --> 20:48.317
saturated in joy.

20:51.384 --> 20:56.115
Second Corinthians says, where the spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom.

20:57.779 --> 21:01.126
Some of you this morning, you need free from fear.

21:02.589 --> 21:04.594
Some of you need free from chaos.

21:04.770 --> 21:08.793
Some of you need free from addiction, anxiety, uncertainty.

21:09.074 --> 21:10.495
The list goes on and on.

21:10.895 --> 21:34.756
I want you to know, when you change the environment, when you change the place where you reside, when you move into the presence of God, there and only there will you find a joy and a peace and an assurance and a foundation that is not shaken when the winds begin to blow and the waters begin to rise and the struggles of life come your direction.

21:34.736 --> 21:35.437
Thank God.

21:36.278 --> 21:37.239
Come on.

21:37.259 --> 21:37.599
Come on.

21:38.841 --> 21:40.042
There's fullness of joy.

21:41.063 --> 21:42.085
Here's what I've discovered.

21:42.165 --> 21:44.668
Peace is not found in a silent night.

21:45.749 --> 21:48.232
Peace is found in a surrendered hearts.

21:51.415 --> 21:52.337
Oh, we're so busy.

21:53.918 --> 21:58.384
We're so busy trying to figure out how do I slow things down.

21:59.785 --> 22:01.848
And I'm not saying that you shouldn't slow down.

22:01.888 --> 22:03.890
We all have this issue

22:04.130 --> 22:06.154
where we go, go, go, go, go.

22:06.594 --> 22:13.787
But what if, rather than waiting for life to slow down, what if in this moment we said, Lord, would you come in?

22:13.847 --> 22:17.734
Lord, I want to walk at your pace.

22:20.038 --> 22:22.443
Lord, I want to allow you to lead my life.

22:23.264 --> 22:26.610
God, I want to allow you to steer my steps.

22:28.738 --> 22:30.460
peace isn't found in a silent night.

22:30.501 --> 22:32.503
It's not found when everything calms down.

22:32.543 --> 22:37.551
It's not found in that picture perfect moment when you're holding that cup of coffee by the crackling fire.

22:37.931 --> 22:45.462
Peace is found when you change the environment and you step into the presence of God and you surrender your heart completely to him.

22:45.682 --> 22:48.987
I wonder this morning, will you turn to him?

22:49.207 --> 22:56.658
Will you allow his peace to invade and truly saturate your life in the midst of the chaos and clutter?

22:57.858 --> 22:59.420
The second truth I find is this.

23:00.662 --> 23:06.651
Peace is not the absence of stress, but the presence of Jesus.

23:06.671 --> 23:07.913
Come on, we've been talking about this.

23:08.814 --> 23:13.802
It's not the absence of stress, but it's the presence of Jesus.

23:13.822 --> 23:17.167
The angel of the Lord said, peace on earth.

23:17.247 --> 23:24.818
Now he wasn't announcing, hey, the moment Jesus gets here, this is gonna be a problem-free zone.

23:26.562 --> 23:28.184
No struggles allowed.

23:28.224 --> 23:30.386
Oh, wouldn't that be fantastic?

23:31.427 --> 23:37.493
Man, wouldn't it be great if we can just say, man, this day, this week is gonna be picture perfect.

23:37.713 --> 23:39.555
I'm not gonna face any problems.

23:39.815 --> 23:41.697
I'm not gonna have any difficulties.

23:41.897 --> 23:43.538
I'm not gonna face opposition.

23:43.879 --> 23:45.921
Everything is gonna be smooth sailing.

23:47.502 --> 23:48.603
Here's the problem with that.

23:48.643 --> 23:55.410
As much as we would love that, we would never grow and mature

23:55.810 --> 24:00.438
in our faith where we need to be if everything was always easy.

24:03.623 --> 24:03.843
Right?

24:05.626 --> 24:10.695
If life was always a slow pitch, there's no problem.

24:12.137 --> 24:12.838
I got this.

24:12.878 --> 24:15.463
I can handle this.

24:17.546 --> 24:22.354
But even though I walk to the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

24:24.290 --> 24:27.675
Your rod and your staff, they come for me.

24:29.277 --> 24:31.260
You leave me beside the still waters.

24:32.201 --> 24:34.564
You make me lie down in green pastures.

24:36.086 --> 24:38.390
This is what the Psalmist David was declaring.

24:38.410 --> 24:50.066
He says, man, even though life is not always easy, and if you know anything about David's story, he had some great moments with God, but he also had some valley of the shadow of death moments.

24:53.058 --> 24:55.525
swords flying at him, spears flying at him.

24:55.605 --> 24:57.029
That's good times right there.

24:59.034 --> 25:03.506
But he realized that he had to rest in the peace of God.

25:06.242 --> 25:08.044
The angel, the Lord said peace on earth.

25:08.084 --> 25:10.547
He wasn't again promising that problems would disappear.

25:10.767 --> 25:17.515
He was proclaiming that God himself was drawing near that the presence of God was going to show up.

25:17.775 --> 25:22.561
The reality is that in this world, we will still have issues and problems.

25:22.701 --> 25:24.904
Jesus declared that in John 1633.

25:28.027 --> 25:33.874
But we can't stop allowing the peace of God to come into our lives just because we'll have issues.

25:35.074 --> 25:39.218
In John 14, 27, Jesus makes an incredible statement.

25:39.439 --> 25:45.485
He says this, talking to his disciples, he says, peace, I leave with you.

25:47.347 --> 25:50.350
My peace, I give you.

25:52.152 --> 25:54.955
Not as the world gives do I give to you.

25:55.716 --> 25:57.438
Let not your hearts be troubled.

25:57.738 --> 26:01.042
Neither let them be afraid.

26:01.506 --> 26:03.448
Now, notice what Jesus says here.

26:03.688 --> 26:09.754
He doesn't say, I'm going to give you just some random peace to hold on to.

26:09.814 --> 26:23.567
He doesn't say, I'm going to give you situational peace when everything comes down, when you have a good day, when the families are getting along, when everything is going just as it should, you will have peace.

26:26.871 --> 26:30.354
But he says, I give you my peace.

26:31.330 --> 26:32.413
Right through stuff around this.

26:32.774 --> 26:40.634
This is the same piece that kept him calm in the boats when the disciples were freaking out because of a storm.

26:42.919 --> 26:43.862
What was Jesus doing?

26:45.085 --> 26:46.789
Taking a nap.

26:46.809 --> 26:48.754
I saw a t-shirt a while back that says,

26:49.026 --> 26:50.048
Jesus took naps.

26:50.468 --> 26:51.210
Be like Jesus.

26:51.711 --> 26:53.093
And I'm like, I need that.

26:53.133 --> 26:54.355
That's glorious right there.

26:54.716 --> 26:59.724
It's the same piece that kept him calm in the midst of the storm while on the boat.

26:59.804 --> 27:03.771
It's the same piece that kept him steady under pressure.

27:03.831 --> 27:10.322
It's the same piece that gave him confidence to follow the plan of God.

27:11.490 --> 27:15.957
You see, having peace in the midst of the storm comes from God and God alone.

27:16.157 --> 27:27.875
It's not something we can do on our own, but through His lens, we can see the storm brewing in the distance, but still be able to see the beauty of God in the midst of the storm.

27:30.399 --> 27:30.620
Hmm.

27:31.902 --> 27:33.364
That's a new perspective, isn't it?

27:35.046 --> 27:36.188
We can see the storm.

27:36.228 --> 27:37.330
The storm's coming.

27:39.682 --> 27:46.495
But we could have enough faith in God to say, Lord, I trust you in the midst of the storm.

27:48.298 --> 27:50.802
Lord, I don't know what you're going to do through this, God.

27:50.822 --> 27:54.028
I don't know how you're going to bring about a resolution.

27:54.068 --> 28:03.666
Lord, I can't wrap my brain around it right now, but Lord, I'm going to see your peace in the midst of the struggles of life.

28:05.154 --> 28:10.080
This piece is available to every one of us in the midst of our clutter.

28:11.261 --> 28:14.726
Paul further emphasizes this in Philippians chapter four.

28:14.926 --> 28:17.489
He says, don't worry about anything.

28:18.771 --> 28:19.391
Come on.

28:19.411 --> 28:23.416
I'm not going to ask you to raise your hand, but how many of you are warriors today?

28:23.436 --> 28:25.178
I didn't say warriors.

28:26.600 --> 28:27.381
Warriors.

28:27.661 --> 28:30.345
W-O-R-R. Worry.

28:30.465 --> 28:31.506
That's hard to say, isn't it?

28:32.002 --> 28:32.823
Warriors.

28:33.244 --> 28:34.386
How many of you are warriors?

28:34.406 --> 28:34.986
Don't raise your hand.

28:35.006 --> 28:36.429
Think about this just for a moment.

28:37.310 --> 28:41.857
Man, if it can possibly go wrong, you are the pessimistic side.

28:42.037 --> 28:44.340
I mean, you look at the glass and you're like, that thing is half empty.

28:44.360 --> 28:45.662
In fact, it's almost dry.

28:45.923 --> 28:47.125
And yet it's almost to the top.

28:48.607 --> 28:49.929
Well, what if this doesn't work?

28:49.949 --> 28:51.191
What if this doesn't pan out?

28:51.411 --> 28:52.613
What if this falls apart?

28:52.793 --> 28:54.035
What if we don't make it there?

28:54.075 --> 28:54.656
What's going on?

28:54.676 --> 28:56.518
Are you worried all the time?

28:56.539 --> 28:59.723
Well, here Paul says, don't worry about anything.

28:59.843 --> 29:01.586
How is that possible?

29:02.978 --> 29:03.759
Well, keep reading.

29:03.799 --> 29:08.486
Instead, pray about everything.

29:08.526 --> 29:23.609
So rather than letting worry be your first response, what if giving it to God and stepping into His presence was the first response?

29:26.473 --> 29:29.778
You see, our first intent as a person

29:30.402 --> 29:33.968
The first thing that we're gonna do is we're gonna fall into the worry trap.

29:35.490 --> 29:36.151
It's natural.

29:38.014 --> 29:40.758
But can I just remind you that this isn't our residency?

29:42.862 --> 29:44.344
We're heir to the throne of God.

29:44.404 --> 29:46.267
We are his children.

29:49.052 --> 29:50.494
And he cares about his children.

29:54.080 --> 29:58.066
And so Paul says, don't worry about anything but pray about everything.

29:59.202 --> 30:03.388
Tell God what you need and thank Him for all that He's done.

30:03.408 --> 30:04.489
Oh, look at this.

30:05.190 --> 30:05.490
Then.

30:05.530 --> 30:07.273
So we had the formula.

30:07.553 --> 30:09.336
The formula was don't worry.

30:09.376 --> 30:11.398
Pray.

30:11.438 --> 30:15.584
Tell God what you need and thank Him.

30:16.245 --> 30:19.028
Then you will experience God's what?

30:20.090 --> 30:20.711
Peace.

30:21.992 --> 30:23.575
Which exceeds anything we can understand.

30:23.615 --> 30:29.202
His peace will guard your hearts and minds as you live in Christ.

30:29.474 --> 30:33.300
Jesus, this word guard literally means to protect.

30:33.921 --> 30:37.187
His peace will protect your heart.

30:37.427 --> 30:39.992
His peace will protect your mind.

30:40.012 --> 30:43.818
Now, this isn't just a makeshift security team.

30:44.119 --> 30:45.862
This is the armies of heaven.

30:46.162 --> 30:55.698
Literally, the word protect here means to protect by a military guard to prevent hostile invasions.

30:57.986 --> 31:03.274
I'm gonna just step out on a limb here and say, I think that sometimes worry is a hostile invasion.

31:05.256 --> 31:10.284
I'm just gonna say that maybe it's an attack of the enemy trying to derail you from your trusting God.

31:11.986 --> 31:26.066
But if we will pray about it, if we would just give it to God, the Bible says that his peace will send out the armies of heaven.

31:27.074 --> 31:29.618
to protect you from the invasion.

31:30.640 --> 31:36.729
There is spiritual warfare going on more often than we allow than we think is even there.

31:37.190 --> 31:37.470
Yes?

31:38.512 --> 31:42.879
Ephesians chapter six, we read it a few weeks ago, we wrestle not against flesh and blood.

31:43.119 --> 31:50.571
In other words, you're not fighting against one another, but against principalities, evil forces of this world.

31:50.611 --> 31:55.058
There's a heavenly battle, a spiritual battle,

31:56.130 --> 32:03.619
And the armies of heaven are working overtime to guard your heart and your mind.

32:03.759 --> 32:12.330
I wonder today, would you trade in all of that for the peace of God today?

32:13.652 --> 32:15.354
Peace doesn't mean that everything is calm.

32:15.634 --> 32:18.898
Peace means that you're calm when he's near.

32:21.026 --> 32:32.583
It doesn't mean that the chaos stops, but it means that as you rest in his presence, as you allow him to guard and protect your heart and your mind, suddenly there's a peace that overwhelms your life.

32:32.643 --> 32:32.944
Why?

32:33.104 --> 32:36.710
Because you've changed the environment where you're hanging out.

32:38.232 --> 32:45.042
Psalm 46, God is our refuge and strength always ready to help in times of trouble.

32:46.306 --> 32:48.828
He stands ready to battle on your behalf.

32:48.848 --> 32:50.290
I want to challenge you today.

32:50.630 --> 32:54.254
Stop waiting for everything to become perfect.

32:54.274 --> 32:59.679
Stop waiting for the chaos to stop, stop waiting for everything to settle down.

32:59.959 --> 33:15.154
But today, choose to adjust the environments, to seek God and let His peace guard your heart and your mind.

33:15.906 --> 33:19.830
The reality is this, peace is not when the storm stops.

33:21.172 --> 33:22.734
Peace is when Jesus steps in.

33:25.677 --> 33:35.207
Number three, when you trade the clutter for peace, you make space for rest and renewal.

33:36.849 --> 33:40.193
Some of you today need rest and renewal.

33:41.715 --> 33:44.818
Some of you are emotionally zapped.

33:45.794 --> 33:48.460
You're relationally worn out.

33:49.422 --> 33:51.827
You're overrun with life.

33:52.949 --> 33:59.002
The clutter has distracted you from what God has for your life.

34:00.645 --> 34:06.738
I'm just going to step out on the limb and say that when we trade in the clutter for his peace,

34:07.330 --> 34:11.938
God in return is going to give you the rest and the renewal that you need.

34:11.958 --> 34:14.523
Look what the angels saying to the shepherds.

34:14.743 --> 34:18.429
They say, glory to God in the highest and peace.

34:19.692 --> 34:21.274
Come on, we're going to talk about that word in just a moment.

34:21.615 --> 34:25.863
And peace on earth to those whom God is pleased.

34:27.245 --> 34:30.751
It's important that we grab ahold of this word, peace in the original language.

34:30.971 --> 34:32.434
It's the word shalom.

34:33.314 --> 34:40.247
Shalom in this context means wholeness or harmony or even restoration.

34:40.347 --> 34:46.439
It's not just a calm feeling in your life, but it's a complete filling.

34:46.479 --> 34:48.082
Not just a

34:48.226 --> 35:15.698
Feeling like I feel good right now, but it's a complete feeling I'm Consumed with all of God when we surrender the clutter to God when we begin to make room for him We are truly making room for renewal refreshing and rest in our lives look what Jesus said in Matthew chapter 11 He says come to me

35:16.418 --> 35:22.765
All of you who are weary and carrying heavy burdens, and I will give you rest.

35:23.486 --> 35:26.530
Some of you just said, that's me.

35:28.612 --> 35:29.132
I'm weary.

35:30.314 --> 35:31.055
I'm worn out.

35:32.456 --> 35:34.879
I've bent just about as much as I can bend.

35:34.939 --> 35:36.881
I'm ready to snap.

35:38.783 --> 35:40.045
Jesus says, would you come to me?

35:41.947 --> 35:44.530
All that are weary and carrying heavy burdens,

35:44.994 --> 35:46.076
and I will give you rest.

35:46.176 --> 35:53.088
Take my yoke upon you, let me teach you because I am humble and gentle and you will find rest for your souls.

35:54.010 --> 35:58.678
For my yoke is easy to bear and my burden that I give you is light.

35:58.718 --> 36:09.778
If you feel weary today, it may not be because your life is too full, it could very well be because your heart is too crowded.

36:13.858 --> 36:19.365
You've let so many things consume the territory that God wants to step into.

36:19.405 --> 36:28.438
You've turned the temple of God into an apartment complex, or for some of you, a subdivision.

36:30.561 --> 36:33.384
And it's consumed with so much stuff.

36:36.368 --> 36:40.594
And Jesus says, would you just make room for me?

36:43.138 --> 36:47.462
Would you just give me space in your life?

36:48.984 --> 36:58.373
Colossians chapter three verse 15 reminds us that we are to let peace, the peace of Jesus Christ rule our hearts.

37:00.215 --> 37:04.599
Let the peace of Jesus Christ rule our hearts.

37:04.719 --> 37:08.283
What are you allowing to rule your heart today?

37:09.784 --> 37:11.826
What's navigating

37:12.034 --> 37:13.816
the course of your life.

37:15.439 --> 37:20.205
I think it's interesting that the author of Colossians here says the word let.

37:22.428 --> 37:32.742
But as I begin to process, I realize that maybe it's because peace isn't something that you force, peace has to be something that you allow.

37:32.782 --> 37:37.328
You have to let his peace rule.

37:38.450 --> 37:41.554
You have to let his presence settle

37:41.762 --> 37:42.483
your spirit.

37:44.226 --> 37:49.154
You have to let his pace become yours.

37:51.358 --> 37:56.487
I read it a couple of weeks ago, Isaiah tells us that they that wait upon the Lord.

37:57.288 --> 38:05.682
In other words, those that trust or another translation says those that rest in the Lord will renew their strength.

38:07.618 --> 38:17.458
Could it be that God's calling you today to make an adjustment to allow His pace, His speed, His direction?

38:17.518 --> 38:21.586
Allow it to be what leads your life.

38:23.202 --> 38:27.028
rather than allowing all the things around you to have control.

38:27.088 --> 38:30.373
What if you would give God control today?

38:30.393 --> 38:38.145
I wanna encourage you to make room for His peace in the midst of the clutter by inviting Jesus into your life today.

38:39.967 --> 38:43.413
Because peace doesn't just come from slowing life down.

38:43.473 --> 38:46.657
Peace comes from letting Jesus in.

38:48.400 --> 38:49.281
Some of you need to hear this.

38:50.804 --> 38:52.306
I'm giving you permission.

38:53.506 --> 39:05.522
this Christmas season to slow down, to take a breath, to simply rest in the fact that God is near.

39:07.825 --> 39:20.082
Come on, some of you need to hear that because you feel an obligation from everybody around you to go and do and make it happen.

39:21.666 --> 39:30.755
You lie down in bed at night and you can't go to sleep for a while because there are hundreds of things running through your mind in your mental to-do list.

39:33.578 --> 39:37.161
Can I just give you permission right now as your pastor?

39:39.944 --> 39:43.347
I give you permission to slow down.

39:44.929 --> 39:46.971
Here's an important word that every one of us needs to hear.

39:47.011 --> 39:48.912
It's a simple word.

39:50.094 --> 39:50.514
No.

39:52.162 --> 39:57.768
Come on, can we say that across all three locations and even online?

39:57.828 --> 39:58.929
Put it in the chat.

39:59.689 --> 40:00.170
No.

40:01.171 --> 40:03.353
Some of you are online or like, I'm not even putting the chat.

40:03.433 --> 40:04.834
No, I'm not putting it in the chat.

40:05.015 --> 40:06.796
No, we've got to learn that word.

40:06.836 --> 40:10.300
No, it's okay to slow down.

40:10.360 --> 40:12.682
It's not easy.

40:15.985 --> 40:20.690
Because when we do and do and do and do, we feel important.

40:22.242 --> 40:23.784
This can't go on without me.

40:25.125 --> 40:27.388
I don't know why I sound like this southern person.

40:27.428 --> 40:28.068
I don't even know.

40:28.108 --> 40:30.511
Southern person with an attitude.

40:32.593 --> 40:33.694
But it's the reality.

40:33.894 --> 40:38.920
We think that if I don't do this, Christmas isn't going to happen.

40:40.802 --> 40:43.204
Did you know that Christmas happened way before you were born?

40:46.007 --> 40:48.370
And it's going to happen a long time after you die.

40:51.874 --> 40:57.079
Christmas is not contingent upon you making a fruitcake.

40:58.881 --> 41:00.283
By the way, nobody likes it anyway.

41:03.126 --> 41:07.410
Just throwing that out there, point number four, truth number four, nobody likes a fruitcake.

41:08.932 --> 41:09.032
Okay.

41:09.052 --> 41:10.734
And not just the person, but the cake itself.

41:13.436 --> 41:15.078
Man, I gotta get back on track here.

41:17.300 --> 41:18.802
But when we allow

41:19.042 --> 41:20.725
his peace to consume our lives.

41:20.965 --> 41:30.320
When we take a moment just to be still, God can step into the midst of where we are.

41:33.124 --> 41:37.751
He can change the environments of what life is experiencing.

41:40.095 --> 41:44.562
And he can take us from this overrun, overlooked,

41:47.746 --> 42:06.273
stressed out, discouraged, tired life into one that's experienced the fullness of his presence, his peace and his joy.

42:08.056 --> 42:11.581
Would you choose today to make room for him?

42:13.524 --> 42:13.985
Let's pray.

42:14.025 --> 42:17.650
Lord, I pray right now that you'll speak across this room.

42:18.978 --> 42:21.822
Lord, speak to every location this morning.

42:23.164 --> 42:32.378
Lord, speak to that person that's sitting in the recliner or at their office seat or in their car or wherever they happen to be listening to this.

42:35.402 --> 42:43.494
Lord, speak into our lives today, Lord, and help us to realize that your peace is available to every one of us.

42:47.420 --> 42:48.882
All we need to do is open the door.

42:52.194 --> 42:52.997
We thank you, God.

42:54.503 --> 43:00.786
Lord, thank you that Heaven's army is ready to battle for us in Jesus' name.

